Local / Sampling-Based Techniques :-- limited number of negative triples dynamically during training.

    1. NegSample
    2. FixedNegSample
    3. KvsSample

----------------------------------------------------------------

Global / Complete-Vocabulary Techniques :-- Strategies score a head-relation pair against the entire graph vocabulary at the same time.
    
    1. 1vsAll
    2. KvsAll
    3. AllvsAll



----------------
Explaination
----------------

Global
-----
1vsall ----   Takes a single true head-relation pair (h, r) & scores it against every single entity in the knowledge graph
KvsAll ----   Groups all valid tail entities that share the same (h, r) pair across the dataset into a single target vector
AllvsAll ---- Evaluates all entities acting as heads against all entities acting as tails across all relationships simultaneously within the batch limits

Local
-----
NegSample ----      Takes a true triple (h, r, t) & replaces either the head or tail with a few randomly chosen entities
FixedNegSample ---- Unchanging set of negative entities
KvsSample ----      Selects a small, targeted cluster (K) of candidate entities for each head-relation pair, scoring the true fact against only that restricted local subset

